description:
&lt;p&gt;The Manufacturing and Distribution Department at Welsh Blood Service (WBS) has a vacancy for a HCPC registered Specialist Biomedical Scientist (Band 6). This is a permanent full time post offering the successful candidate an exciting opportunity to work in the discipline of Transfusion Science at the WBS. The post holder will perform a variety of routine and specialist scientific and technical tasks within the laboratories of the WBS which will include production of blood components, supervision of staff , equipment validation and incident investigation. The successful applicant will work at a level to ensure that all processes meet the requirements of UK Guidelines for Blood Transfusion and EU Directive as inspected by the Medicines and Healthcare products Regulatory Agency (MHRA). As a Specialist BMS there will be a requirement to work variable shift patterns according to the exigencies of the service, including 7 day working, Bank Holidays and requirement to participate in a 24/7 on-call rota. As part of the selection process candidates will be required to attend an interview and assessment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date: 10/11/2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Stephen Pearce&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Manufacturing &amp; Distribution&lt;/p&gt;
